# Mock and remote data sources — [[project_name]]

## Why mock by default

New entities use **mock** data so the app runs immediately without `Constants.apiUrl` or a live backend. Switch individual entities to **remote** when their API is ready.

## Registry — `DataSourceConfig`

File: `lib/apis/common/data_source_config.dart`

```dart
static const Map<String, DataSource> entities = {
  'auth': DataSource.mock,   // when login enabled
  'task': DataSource.mock,
  'user': DataSource.remote, // example after API is ready
};
```

- Keys: **snake_case** entity folder name; `'auth'` for authentication.
- Change one line: `DataSource.mock` → `DataSource.remote`.
- New entities from `add-domain` are added as `mock` automatically (existing `remote` entries are preserved).

Startup calls `DataSourceConfig.validateRemoteRequiresApiUrl()` in `main.dart`. Any **non-auth** entity set to `remote` without a configured `Constants.apiUrl` throws a clear `StateError`. Placeholder strings like `INSERT YOUR LOCAL URL HERE` do **not** count as configured.

`Constants.apiUrl` defaults to **empty** in `main.dart` for mock-only development. Dio uses `Constants.dioBaseUrl` (`http://127.0.0.1` when unset) so DI starts without network calls.

## Infrastructure layout (per domain entity)

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `i_<entity>_service.dart` | Service interface |
| `<entity>_remote_service.dart` | Retrofit REST client |
| `mock_<entity>_service.dart` | Loads `assets/mock/<entity>.json`, in-memory CRUD |
| `<entity>_service_module.dart` | DI: picks mock or remote via `DataSourceConfig` |
| `<entity>_repository.dart` | Single repository; injects `I<Entity>Service` |

Auth (`--login`):

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `auth_facade.dart` | Remote skeleton (Firebase/API — developer implements) |
| `mock_auth_facade.dart` | Mock sign-in from `assets/mock/auth_user.json` |
| `auth_facade_module.dart` | DI for `IAuthFacade` |

## Mock JSON format

Path: `assets/mock/<entity_snake_case>.json`

```json
{
  "items": [
    { "id": "1", "title": "Sample task", "done": false }
  ]
}
```

- Field names and types must match `<entity>_dto.dart` JSON serialization.
- Include **at least 2–3 realistic records**.
- `flutterator add-domain` generates a starter file; **agents must update it** when adding entities manually or extending fields.

Auth seed: `assets/mock/auth_user.json`

```json
{
  "id": "mock-user-1",
  "name": "Demo User",
  "emailAddress": "demo@example.com"
}
```

## Developer checklist — API ready

1. Implement / verify `<entity>_remote_service.dart` endpoints.
2. Set `'entity_key': DataSource.remote` in `DataSourceConfig.entities`.
3. Set `Constants.apiUrl` in `initEnvironment()` in `main.dart`.
4. Run `dart run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs`.

## AI obligation

When implementing a **new domain entity** (epic or manual):

1. Create `i_<entity>_service.dart`, `mock_<entity>_service.dart`, `<entity>_remote_service.dart`, `<entity>_service_module.dart`.
2. **Create or update** `assets/mock/<entity>.json` with 2–3 coherent sample rows.
3. Register the entity in `DataSourceConfig.entities` as `DataSource.mock` unless remote is explicitly required.
4. Repository injects `I<Entity>Service` only — never Retrofit directly.

See also: `docs/architecture/APIS_AND_INTEGRATION.md`.
